- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing social connections and interactions on Twitter. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper explores how social media perpetuates inequalities from the offline world. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper uses advanced image processing algorithms from Face++ to identify gender and race of Twitter users. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possibility as the paper involves image processing and analysis. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely possibility as the paper does not focus on natural language processing, but it does involve analyzing text data from Twitter.
